programme.desc: Powerful, fact-based story of Aids sufferer Ron Woodroof, who smuggled unapproved pharmaceutical drugs into Texas in the 1980s in order to treat himself and to sell to others who were HIV-positive. Electrician Woodroof enjoys a freewheeling lifestyle that includes casual sex, heavy drinking and cocaine abuse, until he is diagnosed with Aids and told that he has 30 days to live. He learns of a drug thought to extend the life of Aids patients, but it is only available in the USA in clinical trials so he sets out to bypass the law and succeeds in creating a supply chain through a business called the Dallas Buyers Club.
